data.title: Carlisle Cathedral
data.meta_description: The Cathedral Church of the Holy and Undivided Trinity, otherwise called Carlisle Cathedral, is the seat of the Anglican Bishop of Carlisle. It is located in Carlisle, in Cumbria, North West England. It was founded as an Augustinian monastery and became a cathedral in 1133 en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlisle_Cathedral More Carlisle photos here: www.flickr.com/photos/davidambridge/sets/72157623465709620/
data.text:
The Cathedral Church of the Holy and Undivided Trinity, otherwise called Carlisle Cathedral, is the seat of the Anglican Bishop of Carlisle. It is located in Carlisle, in Cumbria, North West England. It was founded as an Augustinian monastery and became a cathedral in 1133

en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlisle_Cathedral
